    <chapter>
      <title>World stockpiles</title>
      <paragraph>Nine countries in the world possess a total of 15,695 nuclear weapons.</paragraph>
      <paragraph>The United States and Russia account for 93 percent of them.</paragraph>
      <paragraph>Since their peak in the mid-1980’s, global arsenals have shrunk by over two-thirds.</paragraph>
